.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH deputy 1  "deputy " 
.SH NAME
deputy \- Deputy mode: assign · show · brief · activate · handback (continuity)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdeputy\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Deputy mode: assign · show · brief · activate · handback (continuity)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
deputy\-assign(1)
Assign this regin as the deputy of a role held by a primary
.TP
deputy\-show(1)
Show the current deputy assignment + state + brief
.TP
deputy\-brief(1)
Set the standing continuity brief (maintained by the primary)
.TP
deputy\-activate(1)
Activate on failover (requires \-\-confirmed by the supervisor)
.TP
deputy\-handback(1)
Hand back to the primary when it returns
.TP
deputy\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
